        Product description

        "OLENS" mechanical pencil that magically does not break the lead
        Introducing 0.02 inch (0.5 mm) from the finest model "Orennero" series.
        The "Olens System" will not break the core.
        Tip pipe slides to accommodate core loss It can be written on while protecting the lead so it won't break.
        A single knock will allow you to get the lead out.
        Equipped with an automatic reeling mechanism that automatically releases the lead just one knock the first time.
        One knock allows you to continue writing until the lead runs out. It does not interfere with your thoughts and allows you to focus on writing. Low center of gravity body balance provides stable writing
        The 12-sided shaft used in the body is the image of clumps like metal parts. The body material is a special material that is mixed with resin and metal.

        How to use
        Once knock, the pipe will come out. Write on without drawing lead
        After use, knock and press the tip directly to store the pipe.
        When the remaining lead is low, the pipe will retract with the leopard leopard Knock it several times to remove wick immediately.
        The design is heavy black that you want to keep forever.
        Nero means black in Italy.
        Replacement eraser part number Z2-1N, PPE-2 (with cleaner pin)

        Gp
        5.0 out of 5 stars writes super smoothly
        Reviewed in the United States on April 10, 2024
        Size: 0.3mmPattern: Main unitVerified Purchase
        The pencil writes really crisp and smoothly, although it takes some getting used to such a thin lead size. You have to keep the lead almost flush with the metal tip and the tip will move back when you write. if you use it like a regular mechanical pencil it will keep snapping the lead easily. It also auto feeds the lead so you dont have to be constantly adjusting it. Only complaint is it is a bit thin for my hand and I get sore when writing for long periods, although that is more of a personal preference and not something wrong with the pen. lastly the eraser can be annoying at first, since when you push down on it to erase, the lead will begin to pump out. the eraser is pretty good though, so you can just use less pressure and erase at a bit of an angle to counteract this.
        Apart from this, the quality is really great and feels super nice. I usually prefer fountain pens because mechanical pencils tend to be cheap and plasticky, but this has changed that. I know use this more than more expensive fountain pens. Overall the benefits far outweigh any problems in my opinion
        Read more

You have to keep the lead almost flush with the metal tip and the tip will move back when you write. if you use it like a regular mechanical pencil it will keep snapping the lead easily. It also auto feeds the lead so you dont have to be constantly adjusting it. Only complaint is it is a bit thin for my hand and I get sore when writing for long periods, although that is more of a personal preference and not something wrong with the pen. lastly the eraser can be annoying at first, since when you push down on it to erase, the lead will begin to pump out. the eraser is pretty good though, so you can just use less pressure and erase at a bit of an angle to counteract this.
        Apart from this, the quality is really great and feels super nice. I usually prefer fountain pens because mechanical pencils tend to be cheap and plasticky, but this has changed that. I know use this more than more expensive fountain pens. Overall the benefits far outweigh any problems in my opinion

        E. Sinn
        5.0 out of 5 stars Very Good, bought the 0.5 version too
        Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2023
        Size: 0.3mmPattern: Main unitVerified Purchase
        You have to compare it to other 0.3 mm offerings. 0.3 mm is fragile. It does not work on rough paper. You have to decide whether the other reviews are reviewing 0.3 mm lead or this pencil.

        The pencil is a bit delicate - it is the nature of an auto advanced 0.3 mm mechanism. It is more a pencil for a home or an office worker or a student doing homework at home. It is not for an explorer or a student lugging stuff from class to class in a pouch in a backpack. The tip itself will push a hole in your clothing.

        Rotating the lead is not important since 0.3 is so thin.

        It works wonderfully in an office and for someone who carries pencils in a hard pencil box. You can't press too hard - but that is the nature of the 0.3 lead. If you do the math, 0.3 lead has less than 50% cross-section of 0.5 (I realize the actual measurement is not exactly these numbers.). 0.3 mm lead wears out fast and needs constant advance. The auto-advanced mechanism solves this. This is not so useful for a 0.5 mm pencil because a 0.5 lead does not need advance so often and it does not bother me to advance 0.5 mm lead occasionally.

        With respect to the barrel interfering or scratching, if you write for a while, the barrel will smooth out.

        It is great for lightly marking up a book, making notes on a book, while reading.

        It looks durable enough. I suppose it is not as strong as a 0.5 mm mechanism and if I write 8 hours a day I don't know how long it would last. But for my purposes, marking up books lightly, it is great and the writing looks legible and professional.
